      <intermediateExchange id="ee79c3cb-e3d5-5b15-8437-7c915ebb8551" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e" variableName="CryogenicCooling" amount="0.003834925687337921" intermediateExchangeId="1a91a3f0-e00c-57f0-b1ca-3abeee777b65" activityLinkId="f3f225a7-03bd-54b1-80fa-0ae660f2d8ee">
        <name xml:lang="en">cooling energy, at -25 °C</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Cooling requirements, at temperatures below ambient, for the production of propylene from methanol.

Calculated value, based on the aggregated cooling energy reported by Rodríguez-Vallejo et al. (2020). Namely, Rodríguez-Vallejo et al. (2020) reported cooling water and cooling below ambient conditions (at -25°C) as an aggregate of 9.49 MJ per kg propylene produced. The cooling energy at below ambient conditions was, here, re-calculated based on the stream table available at the thesis of Rodríguez-Vallejo (2021) and the work requirments reported by Luyben (2019). 

References: 
Rodríguez-Vallejo, Daniel F., Gonzalo Guillén-Gosálbez, and Benoît Chachuat. "What is the true cost of producing propylene from methanol? The role of externalities." ACS Sustainable Chemistry &amp; Engineering 8.8 (2020): 3072-3081.
Rodriguez Vallejo, Daniel. "Promoting sustainability in chemical process design using process modelling, environmental assessment and decision making." (2021).
Luyben, William L. "Refrigerant selection for different cryogenic temperatures." Computers &amp; Chemical Engineering 126 (2019): 241-248.
</comment>
