      <elementaryExchange id="7c32e78f-6aa1-57ab-8ae7-2e023a37ad71" unitId="de5b3c87-0e35-4fb0-9765-4f3ba34c99e5" variableName="CW_IN" casNumber="007732-18-5" amount="0.013414001959225505" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="( ( (9.49 - CryogenicCooling)*1000 ) /(4.184)/(43-32) )/1000" elementaryExchangeId="fc1c42ce-a759-49fa-b987-f1ec5e503db1" formula="H2O">
        <name xml:lang="en">Water, cooling, unspecified natural origin</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value, based on the aggregated cooling energy reported by Rodríguez-Vallejo et al. (2020). Namely, Rodríguez-Vallejo et al. (2020) reported cooling water and cooling below ambient conditions (at -25°C) as an aggregate of 9.49 MJ per kg propylene produced. The cooling energy at below ambient conditions was, here, re-calculated based on the stream table available at the thesis of Rodríguez-Vallejo (2021) and the work by Luyben (2019). Hence, this allows the calculation of the energy removed from cooling water with a given temperature difference, 11°C.
References: 
Rodríguez-Vallejo, Daniel F., Gonzalo Guillén-Gosálbez, and Benoît Chachuat. "What is the true cost of producing propylene from methanol? The role of externalities." ACS Sustainable Chemistry &amp; Engineering 8.8 (2020): 3072-3081.
Rodriguez Vallejo, Daniel. "Promoting sustainability in chemical process design using process modelling, environmental assessment and decision making." (2021).
Luyben, William L. "Refrigerant selection for different cryogenic temperatures." Computers &amp; Chemical Engineering 126 (2019): 241-248.
</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.013414001959225505" mu="-4.3114561952463415" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.002125"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="2" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="2" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="2"/>
        </uncertainty>
